Last Updated: 09/08/2025

These Terms of Use outline the rules and responsibilities for doctors who create an account and use the Odyssey Clinic System (“the System”) across any affiliated, partner, or participating clinics. By creating an account, you agree to comply with these terms, regardless of which clinic location you are accessing the system from.

1. Purpose of the System

The Odyssey Clinic System is designed to improve healthcare operations and patient care by enabling doctors to:

Access and update patient medical records securely.

Record consultations, diagnoses, treatments, and prescriptions.

View available medicines, supplies, and services.

Access and update patient billing and service usage details.

2. Responsibilities of Account Holders

As a registered doctor in the Odyssey Clinic System, you agree to:

Maintain Patient Confidentiality

Protect all patient information in compliance with the Data Privacy Act of 2012 (RA 10173).

Never share patient records or information with unauthorized individuals.

Secure Your Login Credentials

Keep your username and password private.

Log out after each session, especially when using shared devices.

Ensure Data Accuracy

Input complete, correct, and up-to-date information for all patient records.

Double-check entries for diagnoses, prescriptions, and billing before saving.

Use the System Properly

Use the Odyssey System only for authorized clinic-related work.

Avoid making unauthorized changes, deletions, or manipulations of records.

Report Issues Promptly

Notify the designated IT or admin team immediately if you encounter technical errors, missing data, or potential security breaches.

3. Ownership and Restrictions

The Odyssey Clinic System is owned and managed collectively for use by participating clinics.

You may not copy, modify, distribute, or use the system for purposes outside your authorized duties.

4. Violations and Consequences

Any misuse of the Odyssey Clinic System — whether intentional or accidental — may result in:

Suspension or termination of your account.

Disciplinary action under clinic policies.

Possible legal action for serious breaches of data privacy or system misuse.

5. Changes to the Terms

These Terms of Use may be updated from time to time. Continued use of the Odyssey System after updates indicates your acceptance of the revised terms.

By creating an account, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agreed to these Terms of Use.
